default The 13.3bn is the sum of the discounted values out to the year 2093.  It equates to circa £1 bn per year
default if the WEBs are held constant in real terms
default year to year
default.
default. 
defaultThe Economic Assessment of January 2012 provides, at paragraph 3.2.1, 270,000 trips per day in and out of 
defaultLondon
default plus 110,000 inter-regional trips, a total of 380,000.  Table 12 of the October 2013 Economic case provides 26% of trips as new, or generated. 
default Hence we have 98,800 generated.  £15bn divided by 98,800 and by 300 days provides £506 or £1,012 per round trip.  Note the 26% is higher than the 24% cited in Table 2 of the January 2012 assessment.
default. 
default The ORR stats provide 1,460 million network rail jou
defaultrneys in 2011-12.  1,460 million times £500 
default(the supposedly WEB associated with each generated trip) 
defaultprovides £730 billion, roughly half the nation’s GDP
default.
